    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Us</h2>
        <p><strong>Husseiniyya Islamic School: A Legacy of Excellence</strong></p>
        <p>Husseiniyya Islamic School, founded in the 1940s by the visionary late Sheikh Hussein, has established itself as a beacon of academic excellence in Bekwai, Ashanti Region. The school's name honors its founder, and its maiden campus is strategically located behind the community center in Bekwai Zongo.</p>
        <p>Under the leadership of Sheikh Abdul Wakeel Kada, son of the founder, Husseiniyya Islamic School has expanded its reach to surrounding villages. The school now boasts several branches, including those in Kortwia-Abodom, Ahwia, Atobrakorom, Kokoben, and others.</p>
        <p>Today, Husseiniyya Islamic School has approximately 650-700 students. The school's growth and success can be attributed to its dedication to providing Islamic studies and quality education.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="academics">
